modules.description: This module defines configuration options for WebSocket connections, including buffer size, error handling, response headers, message encoding, and subprotocol negotiation. It supports creating custom configurations or using a predefined default setup. Concrete use cases include setting up WebSocket servers with specific message handling behavior or custom HTTP response metadata during connection establishment.

This module handles WebSocket protocol upgrades from HTTP requests by validating headers and transitioning to a WebSocket connection upon successful negotiation. It works with HTTP request and response types, along with a user-provided handler that processes the WebSocket descriptor. The child module defines configuration options for buffer size, error handling, response headers, message encoding, and subprotocol negotiation, allowing servers to customize message handling behavior and HTTP response metadata during connection setup. Use it to implement WebSocket servers that enforce custom policies during handshake and manage connection lifecycles with tailored encoding or subprotocol selection.
